Introduction

TEMPEST, also known as TPST, is a six-member South Korean boy group under Yue Hua Entertainment.

On December 31, 2021, SNS accounts were opened, announcing the group name to be TEMPEST. A few days later, on January 3, 2022, the seven members were revealed, in order: Lew, Taerae, Hwarang, Hyeongseop, Hanbin, Eunchan, and Hyuk.

Prior to their debut, Hanbin was known for his participation in I-LAND, Hyeongseop and Lew for their participation in Produce 101 Season 2, and debuting in the duo HyeongseopXEuiwoong, and Hwarang for his participation in Under Nineteen.

The group debuted on March 2, 2022, with the mini album "It's ME, It's WE". The same day, they announced their fandom name to be 'iE', pronounced as "eye".

TEMPEST made their Japanese debut on February 25, 2024, with the release of the mini album "BANG!".

On March 6, 2024, Yue Hua Entertainment announced that Hwarang's activities would be halted due to a lack of trust between him and the company as a result of issues relating to his personal life being leaked on social media. Subsequently, on August 11, 2024, it was announced that both parties mutually agreed to end Hwarang's exclusive contract with the company, leading to him leaving the group.

On July 10, 2024, it was reported that TEMPEST would be participating in Mnet's second season of "Road to Kingdom", called "Road to Kingdom: Ace of Ace". They were eventually eliminated from the show in episode seven, and ranked sixth overall.
